it.jpg|thumb|175px|President pro tempore<br/>[[William R. King]]]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n===House of Representatives===\nThe names of members of the House of Representatives are preceded by their district numbers.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Alabama|Alabama]] ====\n*{{ushr|Alabama|1|1}}. [[Reuben Chapman]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Alabama|2|2}}. [[David Hubbard (politician)|David Hubbard]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Alabama|3|3}}. [[George W. Crabb]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Alabama|4|4}}. [[Dixon Hall Lewis|Dixon H. Lewis]] (D)\n*{{ushr|Alabama|5|5}}. [[James Dellet]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Arkansas|Arkansas]] ====\n*{{ushr|Arkansas|AL|At-large}}. [[Edward Cross (politician)|Edward Cross]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Connecticut|Connecticut]] ====\n*{{ushr|Connecticut|1|1}}. [[Joseph Trumbull (governor)|Joseph Trumbull]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Connecticut|2|2}}. [[William L. Storrs]] (W), until June ???, 1840\n** [[William Whiting Boardman|William W. Boardman]] (W), from December 7, 1840\n*{{ushr|Connecticut|3|3}}. [[Thomas Wheeler Williams|Thomas W. Williams]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Connecticut|4|4}}. [[Thomas Burr Osborne (US representative)|Thomas B. Osborne]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Connecticut|5|5}}. [[Truman Smith]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Connecticut|6|6}}. [[John H. Brockway]] (W)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Delaware|Delaware]] ====\n*{{ushr|Delaware|AL|At-large}}. [[Thomas Robinson, Jr.]] (D)\n\n==== [[List of United States Representatives from Georgia|Georgia]] ====\nAll representatives were elected statewide on a [[general ticket]].\n*{{ushr|Georgia|AL|At-large}}. [[Julius Caesar Alford|Julius C. Alford]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Georgia|AL|At-large}}. [[Edward Junius Black|Edward J. Black]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Georgia|AL|At-large}}. [[Walter T. Colquitt]] (W), until July 21, 1840\n** [[Hines Holt]] (W), from February 1, 1841\n*{{ushr|Georgia|AL|At-large}}. [[Mark Anthony Cooper|Mark A. Cooper]] (W)\n*{{ushr|Georgia|AL|A